  "text": "Let r : R ! R + be a compactly supported positive function, such that the resulting convolution kernel R n × R n 3 (x, x 0 )7 !r(jx À x 0 j) 2 R is a strictly positive definite mollifying kernel of class C 1 c (R n × R n ). For specific examples of such functions see the work by Wendland [CITATION_1] and Buhmann [CITATION_2] for example. For a sequence of e k ! 0 we consider a sequence of mollified kernels",
